name: uncanny cliff
description: You find yourself standing at the edge of a digital cliff, the precipice of the uncanny valley, where pixel art stood back in the 80s and 90s. This sketch was made using Grafx2, a modernized 256-color drawing app that is based off of legendary pixel art programs like DeluxePaintII and Brilliance. It can use colorcycling to animate images instead of frame-by-frame hand animation. This sketch was made back in 2012 and was first shared on the netart chat website dump.fm.
